  "prompt": "What does \"lien amount\" in the SBI mean?",
  "response": "In the context of the State Bank of India (SBI), a \"lien amount\" refers to a specific amount of money in a bank account that is temporarily frozen or blocked by the bank. This means the account holder cannot withdraw or use this portion of funds. Liens are typically placed for various reasons, such as:\n\n1. Loan collateral\n2. Outstanding dues or unpaid loans\n3. Legal proceedings\n4. Tax-related matters\n5. Court orders\n6. Mortgage or property-related security\n\nThe lien ensures that the funds are reserved and cannot be used until the specific condition or requirement is satisfied.",
